# .shopifyignore — DEMO BRANCH
# ============================================================
# Purpose: this branch's only job is to mirror the LIVE STORE's
# merchant-edited CONTENT (templates, global settings, header/
# footer section groups) for version control. Code (CSS / JS /
# Liquid / snippets / layout / locales / settings_schema.json)
# is owned by the `main` branch; demo does NOT track it.
#
# How this file is wired:
#   * Code patterns BELOW are listed as ignored, so a
#     `shopify theme pull --store=... --theme="kitchero-1-0-0"`
#     on this branch DROPS every code file from the download
#     and only writes content files to disk.
#   * Content patterns (templates/*.json, config/settings_data.json,
#     sections/*-group.json) are intentionally NOT in the ignore
#     list, so the pull captures them.
#
# Workflow:
#   1. Switch to `demo` branch.
#   2. `shopify theme pull --store=kitchero-4zilkgr1.myshopify.com --theme="kitchero-1-0-0"`
#      → only content files land in the working tree.
#   3. Commit + push → snapshot of live content saved on GitHub.
#
# `main` branch keeps the OPPOSITE pattern: code is tracked, the
# three content patterns are ignored so a `shopify theme push`
# from main never overwrites admin-edited content on the live
# theme. Expect a predictable conflict on this file every time
# you "update from main" into demo — resolve it by KEEPING the
# DEMO side (this version).
#
# !!! THEME STORE SUBMISSION !!!
# Submitting the theme to the store? Do it from `main`, NOT demo.
# Demo intentionally excludes the code Shopify reviews.
# ============================================================

# === Code files — IGNORED on demo (lives on main) ===
assets/*
snippets/*
layout/*
locales/*
sections/*.liquid
config/settings_schema.json

# === Content files — NOT ignored (this is what demo tracks) ===
#   templates/*.json
#   config/settings_data.json
#   sections/*-group.json

# === Theme Store ban-list — never push any of these ===
*.md
docs/*
references/*
listings/*
.github/*
.theme-check.yml
.editorconfig
.gitignore
.prettierrc*

# Dev-time theme-check config that Shopify's backend doesn't need
.shopifyrc.json

# Node / local dev artefacts
node_modules/*
*.log
.env
.env.*
.envrc

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# IDE / editor metadata
.idea/*
.vscode/*

# Local Shopify CLI runtime caches
.shopify/*
.theme-check-cache/*

# Editor backups
*.swp
*~
*.bak

# Local theme-package zip artefacts (output of `shopify theme package`).
# Pushing one in would create a nested-zip recursion in the live theme.
*.zip

# Local Claude Code agent state — never ship to storefront
.claude/*
.claude-code/*
